The paper deals with the problem of file unavailability in BitTorrent, which is a peer-to-peer network protocol used for file sharing. The paper involves large-scale measurement studies and simulations to explore the causes and potential solutions to this problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.PF (Performance).
